The paper focuses on a problem in robotic manipulation, specifically in grasping an initially invisible target object. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed solution involves deep learning and visual observations, indicating that Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely sub-categories. The use of a critic-policy format and deep Q-learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves interactions between the robot and its environment, indicating that the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant.
